.Dd May 26, 2008
.Dt JEXEC 8
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm jexec
.Nd "execute a command inside an existing jail"
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl u Ar username | Fl U Ar username
.Op Ar jid | Ar hostname | Ar ip-number
.Ar command ...
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
utility executes
.Ar command
inside the jail identified by
.Ar jid 
or
.Ar hostname 
or
.Ar ip-number .
.Pp
The following options are available:
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Fl u Ar username
The user name from host environment as whom the
.Ar command
should run.
.It Fl U Ar username
The user name from jailed environment as whom the
.Ar command
should run.
.El
.Sh "CAUTIONS"
Only jid is guaranteed to uniquely identify a jail.
For hostname or ip-number to work here unambiguousness of one or both
of them have to be assured beforehand.
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr jail_attach 2 ,
.Xr jail 8 ,
.Xr jls 8
.Sh HISTORY
The
.Nm
utility was added in
.Fx 5.1 .
